'''Aero Tropical''', also known as '''Air Tropical''', was an [[airline]] based in [[Angola]]. It was founded in 1996 and shut down in 1999.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.airlineupdate.com/content_public/airlines/africa/angola.htm |title=Air Tropical at airlineupdate.com |access-date=2011-01-15 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120630040956/http://www.airlineupdate.com/content_public/airlines/africa/angola.htm |archive-date=2012-06-30 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
==Accidents and Incidents== *On 27 February 1996 at 05:40 local time, an Aero Tropical [[Antonov An-12]] cargo aircraft ([[aircraft registration|registered]] ER-ACE){{dubious|date=January 2011}} crashed during a poor-visibility approach into [[Lucapa Airport]] following a flight from Luanda. All eight persons aboard the aircraft were killed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19960227-1|title=ASN Aircraft accident Antonov 12BP ER-ACE Lukapa|last=Ranter|first=Harro|website=aviation-safety.net|access-date=2017-08-16}}</ref>
