'''Oghwevwri''' is an [[emulsified]] [[palm oil]] [[soup]] eaten by the [[Urhobo people]] of Southern [[Nigeria]]. It is often composed of unique spices, smoked or dried fish, potash and oil palm juice. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nigerianreporter.com/2015/12/23/tribal-series-the-urhobo-tribe/|title=Tribal Series: The Urhobo Tribe {{!}} NigerianReporter.com: Nigeria, News, Politics, Africa|last=Solanke|first=Simi|website=NigerianReporter.com: Nigeria, News, Politics, Africa|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-21}}</ref>

